&quot;Apollo is brash, loud, arrogant, obnoxious, and egotistical.  Somewhat like I've seen in his father, but even moreso in his Uncle Poseidon.  The difference is, you know most of the time when to turn it down and turn it off.  Apollo is wise beyond his years, but he still has much to learn, for he lacks something we have in spades...and that is Experience.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=hypnos>Hypnos </A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.backtalk.org/shadowydreamer/anime/zagato1.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Silver Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 283<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(2/19/02 10:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=231.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ¤yet another deity.¤</span><hr size=1> ***A small spot of mist appears infront of the group of gods and then starts to get bigger and swirl around as a few raindrops start to fall, and a then with a flash of blue light Hypnos appears wearing a dark blue toga with had small silver stars embroded opon it.*** <br>
 <br>
&quot;Why hello Gaia, Posiedon, and Hades. I just heard all the fuss was about, you know something interesting is bound is happen when Apollo and Posiedon are together, but I guess I'm a little late.&quot; <br>
